. A shuttle driver]", "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/2017859217/"}], "resource": {"fulltext_file": "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service?segment=/service/ndnp/ct/batch_ct_inxs_ver01/data/sn82014519/00414183566/1930091501/0243.xml&format=alto_xml&full_text=1", "image": "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:ct:batch_ct_inxs_ver01:data:sn82014519:00414183566:1930091501:0240/full/pct:6.25/0/default.jpg", "pdf": "https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/ndnp/ct/batch_ct_inxs_ver01/data/sn82014519/00414183566/1930091501/0243.pdf", "segment_count": 20, "url": "https://www.loc.gov/resource/sn82014519/1930-09-15/ed-1/", "word_coordinates": "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service"}, "resources": [{"fulltext_file": "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service?segment=/service/ndnp/ct/batch_ct_inxs_ver01/data/sn82014519/00414183566/1930091501/0243.xml&format=alto_xml&full_text=1", "image": "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:ct:batch_ct_inxs_ver01:data:sn82014519:00414183566:1930091501:0240/full/pct:6.25/0/default.jpg", "pdf": "https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/ndnp/ct/batch_ct_inxs_ver01/data/sn82014519/00414183566/1930091501/0243.pdf", "segment_count": 20, "url": "https://www.loc.gov/resource/sn82014519/1930-09-15/ed-1/", "word_coordinates": "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service"}], "segment_id": "/service/ndnp/ct/batch_ct_inxs_ver01/data/sn82014519/00414183566/1930091501/0243.xml", "segments": [{"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/resource/sn82014519/1930-09-15/ed-1/?sp=4"], "batch": ["ct_inxs_ver01"], "campaigns": [], "composite_location": ["0/united states/", "1/united states/connecticut/", "2/united states/connecticut/hartford/", "3/united states/connecticut/hartford/new britain/"], "contributor": ["connecticut state library, hartford, ct"], "date": "1930-09-15", "dates": ["1930-09-15"], "description": ["Y NEW BRITAIN DAILY HERALD MONDAY SEPTEMBER 15 1930 DOEG IS NEWEST dTENNIS champion Calilomian Wins Spectacular Duel From Frank Shields r New Tork Sept 15 00 A 21yearold Califomian John Hope Pees sat on top of the tennis heap today while experts spent their spare time predicting a wholesale shift in this countrys ranking list Doeg won the National Singles title in a Bpectacular duel with Frank Shields 19yearold New Yorker on Saturday and thus be came the youngest player to cap ture the crown since Billy Johnston first reached the heights in 1915 But more to the point where the question of a new ranking list is involved is the fact that Doeg in his march to the finals eliminated Big Bill Tilden for ten straight years this countrys No 1 player and Francis T Hunter who has been rated just behind Big Bill for some years On the basis of 1930 perform ances there is a strong possibility that at least three younsters Shields Sidney B Wood of New Tork and Ellsworth Vines of Pasa dena Calif may crash their way into the first ten Whether Tilden will lose his place at the top of the list"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2023-06-01T13:37:10.348Z", "group": ["ndnp/ct", "connecticut-state-library-hartford-ct-awardee"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/resource/sn82014519/1930-09-15/ed-1/?sp=4", "image_url": ["https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:ct:batch_ct_inxs_ver01:data:sn82014519:00414183566:1930091501:0243/full/pct:6.25/0/default.jpg#h=397&w=293", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:ct:batch_ct_inxs_ver01:data:sn82014519:00414183566:1930091501:0243/full/pct:12.5/0/default.jpg#h=794&w=587", "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service?segment=/service/ndnp/ct/batch_ct_inxs_ver01/data/sn82014519/00414183566/1930091501/0243.xml&format=alto_xml"], "index": 4, "language": ["english"], "location": ["new britain", "connecticut", "hartford county", "hartford", "united states"], "location_city": ["new britain"], "locati